Based on the concerns raised in the review I have changed the code to make the thread wait for the completion of the previous RPC callback before starting a new one. This is achieved by maintaining a conditional variable per thread. A thread will wait after launching a callback  and is woken up once the callback is done.

Also I'm trying to create a structure similar to ClientRpcContextImpl AsyncClient to make it a go to point for allocations. I haven't figured out how to make it maintain the context and response for the RPC though without it going out of scope so I'll circle around later to work on it.

Also if this looks good next step here would be to attempt to create a state machine similar to the async client,

Changed code logic to Issue new a RPC from the callback of the previous RPC. The thread issuing the RPC waits on a conditional variable and is notified by the callback of the last RPC after the thread is marked complete. All RPC threads then notify the main thread which then cleans up the test and exits. Also added a unit test to run the callback client inproc
